headline: Why International Airline Stocks Are Trouncing United, American
summary: Ryanair Holdings ADR the Ireland-based European discount carrier, is flying high, up more than 40% year to date and just 3% shy of all-time highs.  Ryanair Holdings ADR traded around $63 Monday.  Latam Airlines Group ADR  the dominant carrier across South America, quietly returned to NYSE trading a year ago after its COVID-era bankruptcy, and it hasn’t looked back.

headline: IYT: A Concentrated Approach To The Transportation Industry
summary: Invest in IYT for exposure to top performers like Uber & Union Pacific. Outpacing peers, it leverages economic growth & tech innovation in transport.
